intro: Anasser moluccana, commonly known as the Moluccan anasser, is a flowering plant native to the Maluku Islands in Indonesia. It belongs to the family Araliaceae and is characterized by its compound leaves and small, clustered flowers. The plant typically grows in humid, shaded environments within tropical rainforests. Its botanical features include aerial roots and a climbing habit, which help it thrive in dense vegetation. Anasser moluccana is of interest to botanists due to its unique morphology and ecological adaptations.
